race.comment: FORBIDDEN RIFF (7) was back on track, stepping up to 1500m at Hawkesbury and then went back and delivered this grade at 1800m. Jumps from an inside barrier, and he's an improving galloper capable of repeating the dose. THINK WE'RE THERE (9) missed 1L at Newcastle three back and hasn't had the best of it at his two outings since. This is well within his reach, and Bullock is a key jockey engagement. Gets another chance. DORADUS (6) led and took out a CL1 comfortably at Newcastle over 1900m. Draws to give himself every chance and will take pegging back. MAGICON (4) comes back a few levels in grade with the blinkers applied for the first time. His best form would have him right in it.
